snippet.textDisplay: Never in my life, I ever thought that anything in an art form can shed my tears like this, this is something my heart is crying out loud for years, this is what I have been trying to convey to my fellow Pakistanis, and my friends from around the world. The graphics took me to another world, perhaps the heaven we all believe in. @xulfi Bhai and the coke studio team, thanks a lot. And I wish you all the best. Ahh I want to live in that peaceful graphical world. Where serenity, peace and joy surrounds me. And where hate, lust, jealousy and greed are not allowed to enter. Jazak Allah khair

snippet.textDisplay:
1. What is that minor chord that Zeb sings from 1:13-1:15 “Teri Yaad Nahin” #mindblowing
2. ⁠What in the world is that starting vocal from Nizam??? It’s sooo haunting and beautiful. How did you capture that and nevermind used it as a cut up sample in the beat??
3. ⁠What is that Time Signature change when the video goes outside into another world/Heaven???
4. ⁠what are those minor chords Noorima sings on from 2:19-2:23. Kya change in mood yaar! 
5. ⁠what was the audio production brief on this? Make the music as minimalist as possible and make the vocals come forward as possible? It’s like if we mashed LOFI with Coke Studio PAKISTAN!
Listened to it like 40 times already ❤️
